XLVIII THE SKYLARK

BIRD of the wilderness,

Blithesome and cumberlest, Sweet be thy matin o’er moorland and lea! Emblem of happiness, Blest is thy dwelling·place- Oh! to abide in the desert with thee!

Wild is thy lay and lond,

Far in the downy cloud: Love gives it energy, love gave it birth;

Where, on thy dewy wing‚

Where art thou journeying?

Thy lay ison heaven, thy love is on earth.
